            A Texas native, the Cedar Elm is a resilient and drought-tolerant
            tree that thrives in our climate. It’s a perfect shade tree with
            dense foliage, golden-yellow autumn leaves, and a natural resistance
            to diseases and pests.
          </p>
        </div>

